<br>
Atropos cut another thread with her shears, her eyes as blank as usual.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is it with the male gods and there ego's. Someone filled his head with nonesence making him think he was death...I wonder whom that was. For if it were not for my shears, none would die. &quot; She shook her head.<br>
<br>
Lachesis looked to the youngest of the three. &quot;They are all this way. Our mother, Nyx and our father Erebus, would bicker all the time. It is better to have them believe what they want. The older the God, the younger the child they act when reality is forced against them. Take a good look Atropos, they will all act like this. Thanatos will go throgh many names, in many years, many times. He is no different then the rest of us.&quot;<br>
<br>
Clotho merely nodded. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:times new roman;font-size:small;">@*@ Never tempt Fate @*@</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixlordhadesxi>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/30/03 12:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question of Ego...</span><hr size=1> ::Hades stood there quiety as the Fates quite suddently &quot;ejected&quot; Thanatos from the Temple. Hades listened to their banter and their comments in regards to the male gods, egos etc.::<br>
