 <br>
The Fates were pathetic hag hypicrites. They spoke of Destiny and such as if it didn't matter but at teh same instance they cleared the earth to make there temple last longer. And what was a god without his percification? What was Zeus without his powers of the sky? What was Hades without his power over the Underworld? Just another immortal? No, the people of Greece worshipped the sky, the moon, the sea, and when they did this they worshipped the god or goddess that took domain over that.  <br>
 <br>
When Thanatos was born that is when death was brought into exsistence, but it his powers were only let into the world as Panadora opened that special little box... Destiny was made was created when Fates were created. Thanatos was the god of death, making the power of it, he was not some mere immortal that so lucky granted to use it sparringly. The Fates could cut teh thread becuase death exsisted, all the immortals that created and made up the universe worked in together. The Fates for some reason thought that they could just keep on working without all this.  <br>
 <br>
They were not there in the beginning, Chaos was, they were only another factor of the universe as of every other god. We have our own free will of what to do, If I took a soul the Fates would clip it for they could see that I would take the life out of that person... If you controled all of life, and did not care about it, what reason would you have to keep it going?* <br>
