<br>
&quot;Boy? Is that all you think of me? That is all I am in your eyes? You claim that the minor gods need to be reminded of their place? I can think of Three that need to be reminded of their place as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that, Hades bowed to the Fates, with almost an expressionless face.:: &quot;Yes, I do understand...&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then stepped into a shadow and vanished from their temple::<br>
<br>
::Almost instantly, he appeared in Tartarus, stepping out of a shadow right in front of Thanatos' tower. With that, he entered the doorway and made his way up to Thanatos' room. He stopped at the threshold and looked in::<br>
<br>
&quot;Those Fates have grown pompous and arrogant in their old age. Do you wish to teach them a lesson in humility? For if you do, Lord Hades does have a plan to do so.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hecategoddessofmagic>Hecate Goddess of Magic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/1/03 9:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nefaria.com/gallery/1152x864/art/sorceress1152.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New Plan</span><hr size=1> Hecate left as soon as Hades did.  She realized that now it would be impossible to go after her thread.  The Fates had unsheathed their claws and were preparing to fight tooth and claw.  Hecate shook her head, it was just like her kin to screw things over...again.<br>
<br>
She reappeared in her throne room and one of her servants brought her a goblet of nectar.  She flopped onto her throne and let out a loud sigh.  It had been a long day, but not entirely a waste.  She had learned quite alot, and even now, she was outlining another new plan.<br>
<br>
She drank deeply of the wine, and suddenly she knew what she was going to do next.<br>
<br>
She got up quickly and disappeared in a flash from her throneroom.  The priestesses within the room watched with curiosity and interest.  It seemed their mistress was up to something again.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hecategoddessofmagic>Hecate Goddess of Magic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/2/03 3:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nefaria.com/gallery/1152x864/art/sorceress1152.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Plan</span><hr size=1> Hecate reappeared in one of her conjuration chambers.  She was excited because of a new plan she had brewing.  The room was filled with tomes, scrolls, icons, and other items she had used in the past.  She hurried to the back of a room where she knew a certain scroll was hidden.  Hecate whispered a trigger word and a hidden panel was suddenly made apparent.  She reached within and removed one of the scrolls within the hole.<br>
<br>
As she read the scroll, she began nodding to herself.  As she had suspected, there were certain things she could do to ensure her safety if and when Chaos should arrive.  <br>
<br>
With scroll in hand, she popped back into her throne room and called her priestesses to her.<br>
<br>
::Ladies, as you all know, my foray to the Fates was disastrous.  I may not have gotten the thread, but I did learn of something that could be just as disastrous.  It seems that Chaos is not coming back, but the Titans may be.<br>
<br>
Her priestesses gasped in astonishment, but continued to wait patiently for their mistress to continue.<br>
<br>
::It seems that I, like the rest of my fellow gods have gotten very lazy in our roles.  I somehow have forgotten to keep tabs on them, and now they seem ready to fight back.<br>
<br>
::Most of them have been banished to the darkest pockets of Tartarus.  They aren't dead, just...imprisoned.  I always felt that they should have been dealt with early on, but some of the other gods wanted to be more generous, to be more humane.  <br>
<br>
::How are they going to manage to escape their prison is still a mystery to me.  But it has been a long time since the Olympians defeated them and took over the rulership of this world.  But I have a few ideas as to who might be involved.  It scares me to think of what would have happened if they had won, and if we had been banished.  I've seen where they are being kept, it's not a place I would chose to visit again.<br>
<br>
::But ladies, we love how things are now right?  And I can be pretty sure that the other gods feel the same way.  But based on that last disaster with the Fates, I doubt I can count on any of them for help. Therefore we're going to have to save out own derriers.<br>
<br>
::When the Titans return, they're going to be pretty powerless, but still strong enough for anyone to take out directly, yet powerless to the extent that they can't just mount an attack against us at once.  To regain their power, they're going to have to reestablish a powerbase, which means obtaining worshippers.  Now I know there have always been pockets of Titan worshippers, but never enough to be of a problem to anyone.  Also the Titans have scattered across the world certain icons imbued with their essence.   I have a few of those icons already because I've been using them to fuel some of my spells.  But now we're going to get the rest.<br>
<br>
Hecate looked around the room, and was pleased at the intelligent gleams within her priestesses eyes.  They weren't quaking in fear, but instead viewed this as another challenge to overcome.<br>
<br>
::I'm going to send some of you girls to retrieve those icons.  And some of you girls are going to go kill those worshippers.  I'll be doing this as well, but I've also got a few other things in mind.  Ladies, it seems we're going to have to save the world yet again.  Don't be surprised when you meet resistence.  Just do your job.  <br>
<br>
Hecate whispered more of her plan with her priestesses and then each disappeared in kind to do their part.  Smiling, Hecate looked up to her ceiling ad winked.  She knew she was being watched, just the same way she would watch them in turn.  Waving, Hecate blinked out, and the hunt was on.<br>
<br>
